review_blob: Clear brass colour. Aroma is honey and malt. Taste is, well, ginger. A bit sweet for a summer brew, to be honest.
Clear golden colour with a slight brass tinge. Aroma is pretty grassy. Taste is smooth and crisp with more of a malty character than a hoppy one. Highly drinkable.
Hazy copper colour with a tiny white head that recedes almost instantly. Aroma is a bit sour with some malts. Taste is nice and tart but balanced with malts.
Really nice reddish mahogany colour with no head. Aroma is quite vinegary with some notes of red wine. Taste is fairly tart. Carbonation is pretty low.
Brown with a nice tan head. Really roasted aroma with notes of chocolate. Taste has a bit of sweet milk chocolate with a good, bitter finish.
Clear wood brown colour with very little head. Aroma is quite smoked. Taste is smoky with some sour apples. Incredibly fresh.
Great deep golden colour. Aroma is pine needles and a hint of citrus. Taste is mildly bitter with a dry finish. Delightful pilsener.
Aroma is a lot of pineapple and guava. Clear light golden. Taste is quite tropical with a soft bitterness at the end.
Slightly reddish orange colour. Hazy. Aroma is a fresh herbal tea. Taste has just a hint of cherry. Fantastic.
Muddy brass colour with a thin, somewhat soapy head. Aroma is some pineapple. Taste leads with more tropical fruit and finishes super long, dry, and bitter.
Hazy orange with a nice creamy head. Aroma is citric. Taste is pretty bitter and malty with a lemon finish.
Jet black with a light tan head. Aroma is malt with a tiny bit of coffee. Taste is more coffee with a chalky texture. Warming alcohol only lingering barely here.
Golden and clear as day. Generously large head. Over carbonated. Soft bitterness on the finish.
Hazy orange peel appearance with a pretty dense head. Aroma is strong lemon zest. Taste is much less lemon than expected, with a bready, malty taste.
Slightly hazy straw colour with a foamy head. Aroma is rye. Taste is tart citrus and sourdough bread.

Fuck this is boozy. Like malt liquor boozy. Beyond that, it looks nice: hazy brass colour with a little creamy head. Aroma has some drip coffee and toffee and malt and a shot of wodka. Taste is coffee, toast, and aforementioned alcohol.
From a bottle. It gushed upon opening. Taste is weird chemical sweetness. Aroma is tin. Metallic aftertaste. Atrocious.
Deep and dirty brass colour with a delectably creamy head. Aroma is lots of biscuits and malts. Smooth texture with a medium level of carbonation. Malty taste.
Really light, witbier-style appearance with a good, creamy head. Aroma is woody, mineral, and hay. Nice sparkly texture with a nice mixture of fresh lemons and earthy grass notes.
Deep and dark. Aroma is interestingly fruity with some black coffee. Taste is pretty tropical without any of the coffee notes seen before. Interesting transition that works.
Very slightly hazy hazy golden colour. Aroma is a bit grassy. Slightly sour finish that is a bit offputting.
Clearish golden colour with a persistent little head. Aroma is lots of lawn and wheatgrass. Taste is a bit wheaty with a lot of savoury herbs and a soft citric finish.
Charcoal black with a creamy, mocha-coloured head. Aroma is burning firewood, fresh coffee beans. Taste is dark chocolate and charred wood.
Looks like mud. Smells musky and dirty. Taste has a little bit of plums. Carbonation is low. Not that great.
Slightly hazy brass colour with a small, soapy head. Aroma is bark, wet leaves, and a cigar box. Taste is pretty earthy with a few notes of caramel.

Charcoal colour with absolutely zero head to speak of. Aroma is primarily roasted chestnuts. Taste leads with coffee and hot chocolate with a lightly lactic finish. Alcohol is well-hidden for what it is.
beer_name: Pracownia Piwa Mr. Hards Rocks Milk

review_blob: Really hazy rose bronze colour with a thin white head. Aroma has some barnyard funk. Taste is more tea with some tropical fruits. Carbonation is surprisingly low but its on the border of being okay.
Intensely floral aroma. Taste is moderately bitter and has quite a bit of grapefruit and guava. Nice tropical finish.
Hazy banana peel colour. Creamy head. Taste is a lot of banana bread. Aroma is cloves. Nothing overly special, but super drinkable.

Jet black colour with a very light beige head that is thin and dances around the edge of the glass. Aroma is incredibly smoky and woody, with a hint of sour milk. Taste is a great mixture of chocolate, charred wood, and milk.
Nice slightly hazy bronze colour with a long-lasting head. Aroma is a lot of grapefruit and pine. Taste is medium bitter but without a huge dry finish. Soft texture. Good but not unique.

This is a weird one. Completely opaque colour of dirty brass. Very little head. Aroma is a whole lot of fruits. Taste is crisp apples, grapefruit juice, and vinegar. Texture is weirdly heavy. Fascinating beer.
Hazy bronze colour with a super persistent and creamy head. Taste is pretty spicy, to the extent of becoming unbalanced.
Very slightly opaque bronze colour. Aroma is quite herbal. Taste is really floral and medicinal. Smooth texture. Great!
Deep amber appearance, slightly opaque. Nice creamy beige head. Fairly bitter taste that evens out into a soft, malty finish.
Nice hazy appearance with a slightly reddish tint. Aroma is some rye and grass. Taste is more rye and malt. Not overly complex.

Really hazy orange popsicle appearance. Taste is sweet (with nectarines and a bit of grapefruit) with a tart finish. Theres a bit of an odd synthetic or metallic taste at the very end, which is a bit off-putting.
Really simple amber lager. Colour is a deep amber with a thin white head. Aroma is soft and malty. Taste is slightly toasted and slightly tart.
Jet black with almost no head at all. What is there is soapy and residual with a cola colour. Aroma is big peat, whiskey, and rubber. Taste is whiskey and chocolate. Incredibly low carbonation.
beer_name: Pracownia Piwa Mr. Hards Rocks Peated

review_blob: Hazy peach golden colour with a tiny white head. Aroma is citric, more like a witbier. Taste is somewhat similar to a traditional grodziskie, with a tart finish of grapefruit.
Really full, deep golden colour for a pale lager. Big, soapy head and a really active carbonation. Wheat field aroma. Texture is too carbonated. Taste is a bit corny.
Deep brown with a tan head. Aroma is roasted malts and chocolate. Taste is mildly sweet; you can barely taste the maple syrup, to be honest.
Clear and light copper colour. Dry malty caramel taste. Odd sour and bitter finish.
Dark chestnut colour with a soapy head. Aroma is burnt toast. Taste is roasted chestnuts and malts, but its ultimately a bit thin. Not the best.
Light caramel brown colour. Dense and creamy off-white head. Taste is caramel and malts. Aroma is somewhat grassy with some notes of earth and wood.
Looks exactly like a cola. No head to speak of. Aroma is malt, wood, and dark berries. Taste is really earthy and malty. A bit overcarbonated.
Clear golden in colour. Taste is chemical sweetness. Aroma is pure sugar. Not very good.
beer_name: La Choulette Bire des Sans Culottes

review_blob: Nice hazy orange colour with a rich, creamy head. Aroma is oranges and pastries. Taste is some orange, bread, and clover.
Hazy blonde colour with a super creamy head. Aroma is lots of dill and citrus. Refreshing and light texture with more dill and lemon.
Beautiful clear copper colour. Aroma is malt and and charred wood. Taste has a nice tinge of whiskey and warming alcohol.
